org.pipservices.messaging.queues

Interface IMessageQueue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.pipservices.commons.run.IClosable, org.pipservices.commons.run.IOpenable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryMessageQueue, MessageQueue

    public interface IMessageQueue
extends org.pipservices.commons.run.IOpenable
    Interface for asynchronous message queues. Not all queues may implement all the methods. Attempt to call non-supported method will result in NotImplemented exception. To verify if specific method is supported consult with MessagingCapabilities.
    See Also:
    MessageEnvelop, MessagingCapabilities

      • abandon

        void abandon(MessageEnvelop message)
      throws org.pipservices.commons.errors.ApplicationException
        Returns message into the queue and makes it available for all subscribers to receive it again. This method is usually used to return a message which could not be processed at the moment to repeat the attempt. Messages that cause unrecoverable errors shall be removed permanently or/and send to dead letter queue.
        Parameters:
        message - a message to return.
        Throws:
        org.pipservices.commons.errors.ApplicationException - when error occured.
